=============================================================================================
-EtherDogs is a Simple Multi Protocol Packet Sniffer on ethernet networks.
=============================================================================================
-EtherDogs is Free Software for more information read de COPYING file in this folder.
=============================================================================================

-To install the EtherDogs in your GNU/Linux OS run the Makefile on GNU/Make in the terminal.
=============================================================================================
-To contact de developer send email to josemaria.micoli@gmail.com ou cr4sh.dump@gmail.com
=============================================================================================
-Readme to install correctly this software:
=============================================================================================
-Commands GNU/Make to compile, install clean and remove EtherDogs on yous system:
=============================================================================================
|make;make install;make clean; 	/*to compile;install the program;and remove de trash files*/|
|make remove 			/*to uninstall the program*/				    |
|make 				/*compile*/    						    |
|make install 			/*installing*/						    |
|make clean 			/*remove the trash files*/				    |
=============================================================================================
-This software only run on GNU/Linux Operating Systems and is development on GNU/Linux
Slackware 14.0 x86 but i'm realize the run test and compiling in other distros
GNU/Linux lists any on nexts lines:

	+-----------+
	|-Slackware-|
	|-Debian-   |											
	|-Ubuntu-   |
	|-BackTrack-|
	|-Fedora-   |
	+-----------+

Good luck!

